I"5<p>The Customer Financial Protection Bureau keeps track of all consumer complaints in a database. The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) was established on July 21, 2011, with the goal of fighting for customers’ rights and overseeing customer satisfaction and protection in the financial industry.
The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) provides a list of consumer complaints from its database to organizations for response. Following the company’s response, the CFPB formally publishes the complaints data for the general public to view.</p>
